Another Trump statement, "South Korea is a money machine but they pay us peanuts," is greeted with "howls of inaccuracy" from the South Korean Foreign Ministry and the White House. U.S. Ambassador to South Korea Mark Lippert says "Seoul pays for 55% of all non-personnel costs." (CNN)The National Assembly of the Gambia approves extending Yahya Jammeh's term as President of the country for 90 more days. (BBC) (Al Jazeera)